    - m_Type: 0
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: 
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: 'This is the easiest step in this tutorial, since the setup
          has already been taken care of.


          Double click the "Pivot" blend
          tree. Click the + button and select "New Blend Tree". Set the "Threshold"
          of this blend tree to 1.


          Select the newly created blend tree.
          Call it "Run Pivot". Make sure its parameter is set to "Pivot".


          Afterwards,
          lay out the following animation hierarchy inside the Idle Pivot blend tree:

          *
          -1 | RunPivotLeft180

          * -0.75 | RunPivotLeft135

          *
          -0.5 | RunPivotLeft90

          * 0 | Run

          * 0.5 | RunPivotRight90

          *
          0.75 | RunPivotRight135

          * 1 | RunPivotRight180


          And
          then finally, click "Adjust Time Scale" and select "Homogeneous Speed".




          If
          you play now, the character should pivot during their run like you would
          expect.'
